13:
Oh my. Oh MY!
Ehehe... Ehehehe!
17:
So THIS is where that old saying 
comes from... I can read you like an 
open book, Inaho.
25: I wasn't trying to scare you...
38:
Let's see... "Koizora☆Azuki Style: An 
Illustrated Tale of Forbidden 
Romance."
45:
Well, excuse you! How DARE you make 
fun of KoiAzu?!
51:
KoiAzu is a MASTERPIECE! All of Yamato 
has read it!
Laughter, tears, action! Romance and 
bittersweet farewells!
53:
And most importantly—The main 
character, Kusanagi, is really, reeeally, 
REEEEALLY good-looking.
56:
Oh, is that this guy?
How come he's barely wearing 
anything?
61:
So you can see his—
N-never mind! YOU would never 
understand!
Give it back and go away, Alk!
69:
A story told through pictures and 
dialogue...
I believe we saw something similar in 
the Endless Blue.
70: I would like to read it myself.
74:
Really?! You would? You are going to 
LOVE it, Stella!
76:
KoiAzu is so good! The story is very 
deep too.
This manga taught me sooo many big 
life lessons!
79:
It's an educational text? 
If I read KoiAzu, will I learn to be like 
you, Inaho?
82:
Definitely! Let us dream together, 
Stella!
86:
There's no way it's... Well, as long as 
they're having fun.
90:
I will warn you, however. KoiAzu has 
one big problem.
94:
You mean graphic depictions of 
violence and—
98:
Of course not!
KoiAzu is on hiatus.
101:
So you're left waiting on a cliff-
hanger?
104:
Exactly! The author, Gramp Zigza, goes 
on hiatus all the time.
107:
Gramp? What a weird name. It kinda 
sounds like Grampa.
110:
I suppose? Anyhow, his break this time 
is taking especially long.
112:
How long must fans wait for another 
glimpse of Kusanagi? Maidens across 
the land weep in his absence!
116:
I wonder why he takes so many 
breaks.
119:
He said in the latest volume's 
afterword that he has run out of 
inspirations, and no longer has the will 
to draw.
126:
Perhaps he could find new inspirations 
in some of the books here.
128:
Art and stories from another world 
might give him fresh ideas.
133: I see. What an amazing plan, Stella!
135:
That settles it! I must deliver books to 
his house at once!
141:
H-his house?! You know where he 
lives?!
145:
Of course! I always wanted an excuse 
to visit and ask him to draw Kusanagi 
for me.
148:
And now, I have one! 
No time like the present! Bye-bye!
152:
Whew. Inaho comes and goes like a 
storm.
155:
Agreed, but that's what makes her 
Inaho.
165:
That was fast! How'd it go?
...Inaho?
168:
He DID agree to start writing again, 
but...
175:
It is, and yet... It is not!
Look at the draft he wrote! Look!
179:
Ooh, sure, I'm curious what he came 
up with.
182: Hmm. Inaba? Is this a new character?
186:
Yes, and she is absolutely AWFUL! 
This Inaba girl shows up out of 
NOWHERE, but she already is crawling 
all over Kusanagi!
188:
She talks like a GRANDMA and is so 
stuck-up! Does she think those ears 
and tails make her special? Cute? 
Hmph! I cannot BELIEVE this!
192: I don't know, I think I like her.
195:
Me too. She makes me feel like we've 
been friends for ages.
200:
WHAT?! Why? You two are 
unbelievable!
